   <dc:title>Handwritten letter from Felix Kornfeld to Jeanette Schenker, dated August 23,
    1939</dc:title>

   <dcterms:created>1939-08-23T12:00:00Z</dcterms:created>
   <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2020-02-17</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
   <dc:description>In probably the first such communication since 1910, Felix Kornfeld describes to
    his mother, Jeanette Schenker, his current difficult situation, his deportation to a
    concentration camp and release, his joblessness and divorce, his son (with photograph), and his
    urgent need to emigrate, and asks whether his mother has contacts abroad that could facilitate
    this.</dc:description>
   <dc:subject>Stolz; pride; Näherkommen; rapprochement; Konzentrations-Lage; concentration camp;
    Hindernis; obstacle; Geschäft; business; firm; Geschwister; siblings; Ehe; marriage; Hochzeit;
    wedding; Frau; wife; konfessionslos; non-observant; Jude; Jew; Frontkämpfer; front-line soldier;
    scheiden; to divorce; Bestimmung; regulation; Bild; photograph; Not-Wohnung; emergency
    accommodation; Schneiderin; tailoress; Fusslähmung; foot lameness; Arbeit; manual labor;
    Nachfrage; follow-up inquiry; Gestapo; Auswanderung; emigration; Einsamkeit; isolation;
    Verlassenheit; desolation; Auslandsbeziehung; oversease contact; Kaufmann; businessman;
    Zusammentreffen; meeting</dc:subject>

